  {q:"Which NBA team did Shaquille O'Neal NOT play for during his career?",c:["Miami Heat","Cleveland Cavaliers","San Antonio Spurs","Memphis Grizzlies"],a:3,d:"Medium",p:200,f:"Shaquille O'Neal never played for the Memphis Grizzlies. He played for the Magic, Lakers, Heat, Suns, Cavaliers, and Celtics across his 19-year career — but never Memphis."},
  {q:"Who threw the most interceptions in a single NFL season?",c:["George Blanda","Vinny Testaverde","Jim Hardy","Frank Tripucka"],a:2,d:"Medium",p:200,f:"Jim Hardy of the Chicago Cardinals threw 8 interceptions in a single game in 1950 — the single-game record. For a full season, George Blanda threw 42 interceptions in 1962 — the all-time NFL single-season record."},
  {q:"Which college program has produced the most NHL first-round draft picks all-time?",c:["Boston University","Michigan","Minnesota","Wisconsin"],a:1,d:"Medium",p:200,f:"The University of Michigan has produced more NHL first-round draft picks than any other college program, sending players like Zach Werenski, Dylan Larkin, and others to the NHL consistently over decades."},
  {q:"Who was the first NBA player to score 30,000 career points?",c:["Wilt Chamberlain","Kareem Abdul-Jabbar","Karl Malone","Oscar Robertson"],a:1,d:"Medium",p:200,f:"Kareem Abdul-Jabbar was the first player to reach 30,000 career NBA points, doing so in 1984. He finished with 38,387 points — a record that stood for 39 years until LeBron James surpassed it in 2023."},
  {q:"What is the only city to have two different MLB teams win the World Series?",c:["Los Angeles","Chicago","New York","Boston"],a:2,d:"Hard",p:300,f:"New York is the only city where two different franchises have won the World Series — the Yankees (27 titles) and the Mets (2 titles, 1969 and 1986). Chicago also has two teams (Cubs and White Sox) that have each won."},
  {q:"Who scored the first goal in NHL All-Star Game history?",c:["Gordie Howe","Maurice Richard","Syd Howe","Ted Kennedy"],a:2,d:"Hard",p:300,f:"Syd Howe of the Detroit Red Wings scored the first goal in NHL All-Star Game history in the inaugural game on October 13, 1947. The All-Stars defeated the Toronto Maple Leafs 4-3 in that first exhibition."},
  {q:"Which QB had the highest single-season passer rating in NFL history?",c:["Peyton Manning","Aaron Rodgers","Tom Brady","Patrick Mahomes"],a:1,d:"Expert",p:400,f:"Aaron Rodgers posted a passer rating of 122.5 in the 2011 season — the highest single-season passer rating in NFL history. He completed 68.3% of passes for 4,643 yards, 45 TDs, and just 6 interceptions."}
